# Line-ending policy for files consumed by the Raspberry Pi's POSIX shell.
#
# These MUST be checked out (and exported by `git archive`, the deploy path)
# with LF. On a Windows dev box core.autocrlf=true would otherwise store/emit
# CRLF, which Raspbian's `sh` cannot parse ("Syntax error: word unexpected").
# Scoped to shell/desktop files only — the rest of the tree keeps git's default
# handling to avoid churning unrelated legacy files.
*.sh          text eol=lf
*.desktop     text eol=lf
